abstract: NHL Roundup; New York Rangers defeat Carolina Hurricanes, 4-1; other hockey news noted.

headline.print_headline: Miller Leads Rangers Over the Hurricanes
headline.main: J. T. Miller Leads Rangers Over the Hurricanes

snippet: Miller scored twice in the second period and Henrik Lundqvist made 30 saves on Friday night to lead the visiting Rangers to a 4-1 win over the Carolina Hurricanes.
lead_paragraph: Miller scored twice in the second period and Henrik Lundqvist made 30 saves on Friday night to lead the visiting Rangers to a 4-1 win over the Carolina Hurricanes.
